2025-06-01  David da Silva Polverari <david.polverari@gmail.com>
Version 1.9.3

    [ David da Silva Polverari ]

 * configure.ac: removed obsolete AC_PROG_GCC_TRADITIONAL macro.

    [ Sebastian Pipping ]

 * Renamed bash completion file on install.
 * Fixed several function prototypes and related code to build with GCC 15.
 * .github/workflows/full-check.yml:
   - added GitHub CI test to ensure distibution tarball can install bash
     completion scripts.
   - updated to start covering GCC 15.
 * .github/workflows/man_page_in_sync.yml: created to make GitHub Actions
   enforce man page on release was generated properly.
 * configure.ac: migrated from using deprecated AC_HELP_STRING macro to
   AS_HELP_STRING.

2024-10-20  David da Silva Polverari <david.polverari@gmail.com>
Version 1.9.2

    [ David da Silva Polverari ]

 * Added configure switch to enable existing bash completion.
 * Added dcfldd_error module to avoid dependency on glibc's error().
 * Replaced error() invocations with dcfldd_error().
 * autogen.sh: added checks for pkg-config presence.
 * configure.ac: enabled assertions by default.

    [ Jonas Stein ]

 * Added repology badge with link to all known dcfldd packaged versions.

   [ Lucian Popescu ]

 * Fixed memory leaks and removed unused variables.

   [ Sam James ]

 * src/sha2.c:
   - Fixed aliasing violation on pointer access.
   - Fixed instances of --Wsizeof-pointer-memaccess

   [ Sebastian Pipping ]

 * .github/workflows/full-check.yml:
   - Added build agains musl libc.
   - Added config.log dump on configure failure for debugging.
   - Covered more hashing tests on the expected program output.
   - Disabled sanitizers when building with musl-gcc.
   - Enabled debugging symbols.
   - Enabled use of UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer.
   - Updated Github CI pipeline to use more modern compiler versions.
 * src/hash.c: fixed function pointer type mismatch.
 * src/ouput.c: initialized output_t.stream properly.
 * src/sha2.{c,h}:
   - Replaced SHA2_USE_INTTYPES_H by HAVE_INTTYPES_H to support musl libc.
   - Moved typedefs from implementation to header to allow reuse.

